'''''Jaco''''' is a 2014 American documentary that depicts the life and death of jazz musician [[Jaco Pastorius]]. The film was directed by Paul Marchand and [[Stephen Kijak]]<ref>{{cite web|title=JACO documentary: exclusive interview with film director Paul Marchand |url=http://jazzwisemagazine.com/artists/13920-jaco-documentary-exclusive-interview-with-film-director-paul-marchand|publisher=[[Jazzwise]]|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref> and produced by [[Robert Trujillo]] of [[Metallica]] and [[John Battsek]] of [[Passion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jaco: The Film Is Now Available on Netflix|url=https://www.bassplayer.com/artists/jaco-the-film-is-now-available-on-netflix|publisher=[[Bass Player (magazine)|Bass Player]]|date=February 20, 2018|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref> 

The film features interviews with [[Herbie Hancock]], [[Wayne Shorter]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Joni Mitchell]], [[Carlos Santana]], [[Jerry Jemmott]], [[Jonas Hellborg]], [[Bootsy Collins]], and [[Flea (musician)|Flea]].<ref name="why">{{cite web|last1=Ragusea|first1=Adam|title=Why Metallica's Bassist Is Producing A Jazz Documentary|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/ablogsupreme/2014/04/18/304532782/why-metallicas-bassist-is-producing-a-jazz-documentary|website=NPR.org|accessdate=26 June 2017|date=18 April 2014}}</ref>

==Reception==
''[[The New York Times]]'' called ''Jaco'' "an illuminating, compassionate new documentary."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Chinen|first=Nate|title=‘Jaco,’ a Documentary About the Jazz Musician Jaco Pastorius|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/28/arts/music/review-jaco-a-documentary-about-the-jazz-musician-jaco-pastorius.html|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|date=November 27, 2015|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Decider (website)|Decider]]'' pronounced it "an engaging and interesting documentary" albeit about a "musician’s musician" which could limit it's appeal.<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Benjamin H.|title=‘Jaco’ Documentary Profiles Troubled Jazz Fusion Bass Virtuoso |url=https://decider.com/2016/07/01/jaco-documentary-netflix/|publisher=[[Decider (website)|Decider]]|date=July 1, 2016|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref> Bassist [[Billy Sheehan]] felt that it was "a wonderful film" but opined that "I think, maybe, it might have concentrated on some eccentricities a little bit more than it could have."<ref>{{cite web|last=Hartmann|first=Graham|title=Billy Sheehan Remembers Jamming With Jaco Pastorius + Talks ‘Jaco’ Documentary|url=https://loudwire.com/billy-sheehan-jamming-jaco-pastorius/|publisher=[[Loudwire]]|date=February 22, 2017|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref> 

